one month ago you got called back home to God. for what, i can never question. 

the pain is so immeasurable to know i can’t see, hear or talk to you again. but i understand and reconcile emotions as best as i can. 

i feel your presence heavily. walking with me, guiding me and pushing me where i need to go. i know you never left me on this path of life, you’re just a little bit further up the trail. 

“we owe our kids an educations. they’re a blank page for us to write on.” - D.W.

i’m so thankful you were my author and wrote volumes of knowledge within me. 

i love you. i miss you.
and i cannot wait to see you again dad. 

thank you for everything.
